HEADWORD: Stonewort
<hw>Stone"wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Any plant of the genus Chara; -- so called because they are often
incrusted with carbonate of lime. See <er>Chara</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stonily</ent>⟦br⟧
